villain /ˈvɪlən/

(villains) 

1. N-COUNT A villain is someone who deliberately harms other people or breaks the law in order to get what he or she wants. 恶棍 

例： I left the room, feeling like a villain and a murderer. 我离开了那个房间，感觉自己就像一个恶棍，一个杀人犯。 

2. N-COUNT The villain in a novel, movie, or play is the main bad character. (小说、电影、戏剧中的) 反面主角 

例： He also played a villain opposite Sylvester Stallone in Demolition Man (1992). 他在1992年的影片《超级战警》中扮演了一个与西尔维斯特·史泰龙敌对的反面主角。

